meta {
  name: POST honk-and-flash (FLASH_ONLY)
  type: http
  seq: 11
}

post {
  url: {{base_url}}/api/v1/vehicle-access/{{vin}}/honk-and-flash
  body: json
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
  Content-Type: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "mode": "FLASH_ONLY"
  }
}

docs {
  Triggers the hazard lights to flash so the user can locate the car.
  We always send mode=FLASH_ONLY (no horn) — the integration exposes
  only the flash button, never the honk variant, to be neighbour-
  friendly. Other valid modes per myskoda: HONK_AND_FLASH.

  No S-PIN required (mysmob doesn't gate this command).

  Implementation: SkodaClient.command_flash() in
  custom_components/vag_connect/cariad/api/skoda.py:453. The
  latitude/longitude params on the helper are ignored — Skoda
  mysmob doesn't need them in the body unlike CARIAD-BFF.
}
